t Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Bryde was born in 1238, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mabel de Adlington."},"et":{"1238–":"1238–Surnud","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1262–1332":"1262–1332","1238–Male":"1238–Surnud","1238":"1238","1332":"1332","1275":"1275","1262":"1262","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ormskirk, Lancashire, England":"Ormskirk, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1238–":"1238–Kuollut","1275–Female":"1275–Kuollut","1262–1332":"1262–1332","1238–Male":"1238–Kuollut","1238":"1238","1332":"1332","1275":"1275","1262":"1262","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ormskirk, Lancashire, England":"Ormskirk, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1238–":"1238–Décédé","1275–Female":"1275–Décédée","1262–1332":"1262–1332","1238–Male":"1238–Décédé","1238":"1238","1332":"1332","1275":"1275","1262":"1262","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ormskirk, Lancashire, England":"Ormskirk, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Bryde est né en 1238, à Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mabel de Adlington."},"de":{"1238–":"1238–Verstorben","1275–Female":"1275–Verstorben","1262–1332":"1262–1332","